			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The effect on <em>fetches</em> is immediate. The effect on actual output pixels is delayed until the already-fetched pattern data passes through the shift registers that decode planar tile format and perform fine scrolling.<br /><br />Requests for edits like <a href="https://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php?title=PPU_scrolling&amp;curid=192&amp;diff=14176&amp;oldid=14044" class="postlink">this</a> to address cross-cutting concerns everywhere, such as how the timing of mid-scanline <em>v</em> changes interacts with the pixel decoding and fine scroll processes, are part of how the wiki becomes more verbose and harder for a novice to read.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
